 maps, and together the three names float in the bowl like three moons, and the relic-needle’s point kisses their reflections without breaking them. The ghost lights circle in widening rings, and the straight water eases as if its shoulders have been rubbed by kind hands, because burdens shared weigh differently. \", \"outcome\": \"The queen smiles with the sound reeds make in a forgiving wind and accepts the braided name, agreeing to safe passage that does not ask for shadows so long as the braid is rewoven each Fogfast in a simple public rite where children blow reed-flutes and elders name those they aid. The Accord sets shared stewardship and forbids predatory terms by tying any levy to a triad’s consent, and it names a practice of reparations paid in peat work, seed exchange, and lantern-keeping rather than in raw coin alone, which proves harder to game and easier to honor. The relic-needle is returned beneath a willow canopy where Order and Willowwife wash it together, and it no longer hums with suspicion but with a low, satisfied note when liars approach, which both factions quietly appreciate for different reasons. Kezra receives a safe-passage token woven by Ossa’s own hands, and even the canal murk near the Floodwalk seems to move aside when it is shown, because the token remembers the children’s music. Over the next seasons the moth frames fatten, pilots whistle without fear on the straight cut, and though the Night Cartographers grieve the loss of an expensive fear, they quickly turn to selling maps of the new rite’s songs, which is a better business for everyone’s sleep.\"}\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M8\"], \"next\": [\"M10\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"Token\", \"description\": \"Safe-passage token woven of bone-white reeds that carries the queen’s forbearance, granting advantages in the Mourning Mire and on certain canal routes when shown at dusk-lit waters.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"Relic\", \"description\":